ie traditionellen Gräben zwischen »uns« und »den Anderen« ein, und es entstehen neue Spielfelder einer jungen, engagierten Wissenschaft und Praxis.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aColonizationxHistory. 0aColonizationxSocial aspects. 0aEthnophilosophyxHistory. 4aEthnologie. 4aKolonialismus. 4aKultur. 4aKulturanthropologie. 4aRezeptionsanalyse. 4aWriting Culture. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aCultural Anthropology.  aCulture.  aEthnology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Highlight Collection Complete Package 2000-2009z9783110463415oZDB-23-TSO08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Highlight Collection Geschichte 2000-2009z978311046334740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839401019zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839401019423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839401019/original  a978-3-11-046334-7  transcript Highlight Collection Geschichte 2000-2009c2000d2009  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-TSOc2000d2009